I"y<p>I am very particular about who I spend my time with. I am close with only around a dozen people from work. By ‘work’, I mean all the places I have ever worked at. Similarly, I can count the number of friends I have. It is hard to maintain friendships when you say <a href="https://manassaloi.com/2020/01/01/getting-shit-done-happiness.html">No</a> to most things. But the people that I am fortunate to have in my life, I can call them even at midnight. I can open up to them, talk without being judged. Nor do I judge them. I am free to be myself with them. Maybe, I can even do a startup with them someday, if I want.  </p>
